You're seeing this error because Helm timed out while trying to uninstall the Rancher release:

Error: uninstallation completed with 1 error(s): 
* timed out waiting for the condition

This usually happens when some Kubernetes resources (like webhooks, finalizers, or CRDs) are stuck and prevent the release from being fully deleted.


---

‚úÖ Fix Step-by-Step


---

üßº Step 1: Force Remove Finalizers (Clean Up Stuck Resources)

1. Check for any Rancher-related namespaces stuck in Terminating:



kubectl get namespaces

If you see cattle-system or others stuck in Terminating, do this:

2. Remove finalizers:



kubectl get namespace cattle-system -o json \
| jq '.spec.finalizers = []' \
| kubectl replace --raw "/api/v1/namespaces/cattle-system/finalize" -f -

If jq is not installed, let me know ‚Äî I‚Äôll show you another way.


---

üßπ Step 2: Manually Delete the Helm Release

Even though Helm failed, the release metadata may still exist. Use this:

helm uninstall rancher -n cattle-system --no-hooks

This skips running any uninstall hooks that might be causing the hang.


---

üßæ Step 3: Double-Check Deletion

Clean up any leftover resources manually:

kubectl delete ns cattle-system --grace-period=0 --force

‚ö†Ô∏è --force is aggressive, use only if you're sure you're wiping Rancher completely.


---

üîÅ Step 4: Retry Installation

Once everything is cleaned:

helm install rancher rancher-latest/rancher \
  --namespace cattle-system \
  --create-namespace \
  --set hostname=rancher.local \
  --set replicas=1


---

Let me know if you get stuck on any step, especially if jq isn‚Äôt installed or namespace isn‚Äôt terminating.

